==English==
===Noun===
'''perfect number''' (''plural'' '''perfect numbers''')

#(''mathematics'') A number that is the sum of all of its [[divisor]]s except itself.
#:''The factors of 28 are 1, 2, 4, 7, 14 and 28, and 1 + 2 + 4 + 7 + 14 = 28, so 28 is a '''perfect number'''.''

